OL,6,FOne adjudicator Peredur Lynch wrote of
OL,7,FMr Hallam's poem: "When I first read
OL,8,Fthis lively opening to the awdl (a
OL,9,Flong poem), I must admit my
OL,10,Finstinctive reaction was something
OL,11,Flike: 'Very entertaining, but it'll
OL,12,Ftake more than a cheeky cywydd
OL,13,F(couplet) like this to win the
OL,14,FNational Chair.' And then, turning to
OL,15,Fthe second section, I was hit with a
OL,16,Fgut punch`the line: 'Six months? Ten
OL,17,Fmonths? A little more?'
