OL,3,CPoet who documented cancer struggle
OL,4,Cwins prestigious Eisteddfod chair
OL,6,F"Without warning, we are transported
OL,7,Ffrom the football pitch to Glangwili
OL,8,FHospital, where the poet receives a
OL,9,Fdiagnosis of bone cancer and (it
OL,10,Fappears) metastatic cancer in the
OL,11,Fliver. I said earlier I was deceived.
OL,12,FAnd life is a deceiver. One day, a
OL,13,Ffootball pitch full of challenge and
OL,14,Fbravado; the next, a world turned
OL,15,Fupside down."
